Sound-effect assets

The WAV files in assets/sfx/ are generated locally by procedural and
recording-driven generators and are CC0-derived: procedural cues are pure DSP
synthesis (public-domain-equivalent by construction), and hybrid cues layer
only CC0 or public-domain source recordings. They carry no standalone-use
restriction and may be freely used, modified, and redistributed. Per-file
provenance, the generator and command behind each, and every CC0 source
recording are recorded in docs/asset-sources.md and docs/audio-provenance.json.
